{
 "name": "RPlog_Dining_on_Danger_at_the_Red_Dragon",
 "title": "Dining on Danger at the Red Dragon",
 "summary": "A New Republic delegation, Senator Tokoga and Ambassador Ambrosia Delgard, slips into Coronet City on Corellia under heavy Imperial security to meet a trio of Corellian resistance leaders at a sympathetic baker's house, escorted by the marine Rhannak and the watchful Commander Rasi. The rebel spokesman Adler presses the Republicans on what they truly want for Corellia, testing whether they intend to free the planet or merely absorb it; Delgard insists the Republic seeks only to help Corellia choose its own future, while Tokoga confirms that promised medical and munitions supplies are already being run in aboard the Rapier. Adler agrees to lend the resistance's influence in exchange for ample supplies and proof the Republic can beat the Empire on Corellia through raids and operations. He requests experienced soldiers to help plan those operations, taking a particular interest in Rhannak, whom his burly companion has taken a liking to. The meeting ends with Tokoga agreeing to assign advisory officers, the alliance tentatively sealed.",
